{"TopicId":146537,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"What To Name Planets Around Proxima Centauri?","CreatedByName":"ProtoJeb21","CreatedById":153551,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T19:37:02Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"ProtoJeb21","CreatedById":153551,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T19:37:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo recently, the ESO confirmed the existence of an Earth-mass planet around our nearest star, the midgety red dwarf \u003Cstrong\u003EProxima Centauri\u003C/strong\u003E. Because of how monumental this discovery is, it\u0027s only fitting to give Proxima b a name. What do you think it should be named? Also, since there appears to be at least one other hard-to-detect planet in the system, what should other planets orbiting Proxima be named?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI like to call Proxima b \u003Cstrong\u003EFeronia\u003C/strong\u003E, after the Roman goddess of the Earth, nature, health, and fertility. Since this system is so close to us, I feel like giving it the Greco-Roman naming convention we use for our solar system.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Shpaget","CreatedById":45577,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T19:51:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would be a poor name if it turns out it\u0027s a scorched dry desert, as it probably is.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ProtoJeb21","CreatedById":153551,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T19:54:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729677\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146537\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472154716\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002245577\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Shpaget\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Shpaget said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would be a poor name if it turns out it\u0027s a scorched dry desert, as it probably is.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnly if the orbital eccentricity is high. If not, then it could either be a Warm Terra or a Temperate Desert. Let\u0027s hope for a low eccentricity....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T19:56:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBased on what I\u0027ve seen in No Man\u0027s Sky, I think it\u0027ll likely be named\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nPlanet McPlanetyFace\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nPoopworld\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u0026lt;Name\u0026gt;\u0027s Awesome Planet\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Findthepin1","CreatedById":139989,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T20:00:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729683\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146537\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472154887\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022153551\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ProtoJeb21\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, ProtoJeb21 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnly if the orbital eccentricity is high. If not, then it could either be a Warm Terra or a Temperate Desert. Let\u0027s hope for a low eccentricity....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIts equilibrium temperature is -39 degrees Celsius. That\u0027s 21 degrees lower than Earth. It\u0027s probably colder, then, even with a thicker atmosphere, IMO.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bill Phil","CreatedById":127797,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T20:41:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d say we shouldn\u0027t name it until someone or thing goes there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Green Baron","CreatedById":107381,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-25T21:11:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOf course, you can call it as you like, no problem ... buuuut, the discoverer(s) have to right to name an object and they sticked to the usual nomenclature.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust sayin\u0027\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n:-)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GoSlash27","CreatedById":111526,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-26T00:55:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729687\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146537\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472155016\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBased on what I\u0027ve seen in No Man\u0027s Sky, I think it\u0027ll likely be named\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nPlanet McPlanetyFace\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nPoopworld\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u0026lt;Name\u0026gt;\u0027s Awesome Planet\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlanet \u0022Bob\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"CptRichardson","CreatedById":269,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-26T01:23:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt shall be named by committee, only after we figure out what we\u0027re dealing with. It\u0027s our closest neighbor ever, and the only exoplanet that can be feasibly be visited within a human lifetime depending on how crazy we book it.\u00A0 We\u0027ve got one shot to properly naming this sort of thing, we need to get it right.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr we could call it \u0027Bob\u0027. Bob works.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Robotengineer","CreatedById":104525,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-26T03:03:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729687\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146537\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472155016\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn August 25, 2016 at 2:56 PM, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBased on what I\u0027ve seen in No Man\u0027s Sky, I think it\u0027ll likely be named\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nPlanet McPlanetyFace\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nPoopworld\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u0026lt;Name\u0026gt;\u0027s Awesome Planet\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nForgot Harambe memes.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729743\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146537\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472157666\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127797\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bill Phil\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn August 25, 2016 at 3:41 PM, Bill Phil said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d say we shouldn\u0027t name it until someone or thing goes there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLike we did with all the\u00A0celestial bodies in the solar system?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust don\u0027t let the people at \u003Ca href=\u0022http://nameexoworlds.iau.org\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://nameexoworlds.iau.org\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0name it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCheckout this proposal for Epsilon Eridani\u00A0(a perfectly fine name to begin with) and its planet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022\u003Cstrong style=\u0022color:rgb(0,0,0);font-family:\u0027Open Sans\u0027, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EGejalbis\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(0,0,0);font-family:\u0027Open Sans\u0027, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:14px;background-color:rgb(245,245,245);\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr style=\u0022color:rgb(0,0,0);font-family:\u0027Open Sans\u0027, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(153,153,153);font-family:\u0027Open Sans\u0027, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EOur group has realized it would be a best option to create a random name with no meaning for both the star and the planet, remembering that each and every word in all languages were, in the beginning no more than a random sound to which was used to represent a concept. To give a clearer example, much before becoming the name of the biggest planet of our Solar System, \u201CJupiter\u201D was only a sound that was used by the first Latins to refer to their god of the storms (and then the planet). By proposing such names, we intend to create a similar effect.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003E\u0022\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022\u003Cstrong style=\u0022color:rgb(0,0,0);font-family:\u0027Open Sans\u0027, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EStafar31\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(0,0,0);font-family:\u0027Open Sans\u0027, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:14px;background-color:rgb(245,245,245);\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr style=\u0022color:rgb(0,0,0);font-family:\u0027Open Sans\u0027, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(153,153,153);font-family:\u0027Open Sans\u0027, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EConsidering there is no known information of how the planet looks like, only artistic conceptions, we can\u2019t name this planet after its appearence (like Neptune, which has been named after the roman sea god because of its bluish color). Therefore, we suggest a name that has no meaning behind it with a random number\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Open Sans\u0027, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u0022\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Open Sans\u0027, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EProxima Centauri B is a fine name.\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-27T22:20:28Z\u0022 title=\u002208/27/2016 10:20  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 27, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Robotengineer\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EAlpha Centauri B?! What was I thinking?\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"UmbralRaptor","CreatedById":2767,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-26T03:04:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProxima Cen b\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nClever mythological name can wait until we have some actual data on it. (And confirmation that it exists)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222730217\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146537\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472180595\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022104525\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Robotengineer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Robotengineer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Open Sans\u0027, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EAlpha Centauri B is a fine name.\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alpha_Centauri_B\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EEr, there\u0027s already a star with that name.\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-26T03:07:51Z\u0022 title=\u002208/26/2016 03:07  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 26, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by UmbralRaptor\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scotius","CreatedById":57622,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-26T03:24:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTema. TErra-MArs. It\u0027s from polish sci-fi book aptly named \u0022Proxima\u0022 - in which crew of interstellar expedition finds a (barely) habitable planet that is the size of Earth, but the climate is more similiar to Mars (except from oases artificially created by aliens to help preserve local life that thrived in the past, before climate deteriorated.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ten Key","CreatedById":123319,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-26T03:31:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nemesis_(Asimov_novel)\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EErythro\u003C/a\u003E?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Motokid600","CreatedById":66349,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-26T03:47:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022tumblr_lxl0m8ZaE51qinmdwo5_r1_500.gif\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://33.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_lxl0m8ZaE51qinmdwo5_r1_500.gif\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mitchz95","CreatedById":82292,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-26T03:51:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think it\u0027s best to wait until we know more about it. Until then, we might as well just call it Prox b.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPotential names from literature: Per Ardua, Furon, Trisolaris.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"legoclone09","CreatedById":142607,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-26T04:36:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222730217\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146537\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472180595\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022104525\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Robotengineer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Robotengineer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nForgot Harambe memes.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI vote to call the planet Haramberniesanders.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mycroft","CreatedById":158484,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-26T04:37:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProbably not the most unique\u00A0idea, but we should name one after \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/4-harvester/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u00224\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/4-harvester/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@HarvesteR\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GDJ","CreatedById":58462,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-26T05:07:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI vote for \u0022Bob\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rakaydos","CreatedById":101988,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-26T06:34:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWunderland\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNamed for famus science fiction worlds around the same stars.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-26T06:34:42Z\u0022 title=\u002208/26/2016 06:34  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 26, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Rakaydos\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Streetwind","CreatedById":98962,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-26T06:49:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot really, no. Wunderland was in orbit around the binary system Alpha Centauri, not around Proxima Centaury which is a different star (albeit a good buddy of the binary pair).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStill one of the better suggestions in this thread - it\u0027s easy to pronounce in many languages, and suggests a sense of awe at the discovery. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-26T07:49:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003EEreshkigal\u003C/em\u003E as she lurks in a murrey dusk and is dry and lifeless.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003ENephthys\u003C/em\u003E if things are not so bad.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, there is a lack of Ancient Egyptian deities in the sky, while Toliman \u0026amp; Proxima give a decent possibility.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KSK","CreatedById":61025,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-26T07:53:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sid_Meier%27s_Alpha_Centauri\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EChiron\u003C/a\u003E of course. Known to its eventual residents simply as Planet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kryten","CreatedById":348,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-26T09:47:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you want to be proper, the current name isn\u0027t Proxima b, it\u0027s Alpha Centauri Cb. Proxima b is already a widely accepted colloquial name, so why not keep using that?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DDE","CreatedById":146349,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-26T09:53:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729687\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146537\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472155016\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBased on what I\u0027ve seen in No Man\u0027s Sky, I think it\u0027ll likely be named\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nPlanet McPlanetyFace\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nPoopworld\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u0026lt;Name\u0026gt;\u0027s Awesome Planet\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou made me!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022exoplanet_names.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://imgs.xkcd.com/comics/exoplanet_names.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022exoplanet_names_2.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://imgs.xkcd.com/comics/exoplanet_names_2.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI vote for Kepler 296 B variant.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-26T09:56:37Z\u0022 title=\u002208/26/2016 09:56  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 26, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by DDE\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nikolai","CreatedById":23085,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-26T11:15:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222729690\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146537\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472155222\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139989\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Findthepin1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 hours ago, Findthepin1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIts equilibrium temperature is -39 degrees Celsius. That\u0027s 21 degrees lower than Earth. It\u0027s probably colder, then, even with a thicker atmosphere, IMO.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust the opposite, actually, if the planet in question has greenhouse gases.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.astro.princeton.edu/~strauss/FRS113/writeup3/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.astro.princeton.edu/~strauss/FRS113/writeup3/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}